(thirdQuint)A Feasibility Study to Evaluate Skin Cleansing With a Sodium Hypochlorite Wash.

 This is a feasibility study in approximately 20 subjects over a 5-week period per subject.

 The study will investigate the rate of infection with subjects undergoing elective lower extremity arterial bypass graft surgery or femoral endarterectomy.

 The subjects are instructed to shower with the sodium hypochlorite body wash daily, or as modified by the physician, for 5 of the 7 days leading to their surgery.

